content.description:
Climb the short crack near the center of the amphitheater up to the right side of the same ledge as Furious Funnel. Climb over or around the block and the bush/tree protecting the acute dihedral, then stem or face climb your way up the dihedral to the top.

 Except for the bush/tree, it's an interesting climb. This is unnamed #12 in Swartling/Mayer.
content.location: Located in the middle of the main face in the Lost Temple amphitheater between Furious Funnel and Nemesis.

content.description: This is fine route and if worth climbing assuming  you are already at Lost Temple.
content.protection: Nemesis would be hard to protect.
content.location: The route is to the left of Lost Temple Corner.  Start on the left side of the corner pedestal.  Continue straight up steep face.  Finish on the ledge to the right of the overhang.

content.description:
Hug the initial pillar, stem the smooth corner, and then easier climbing with great finger & hand jams to the top. 

  Among the best 5.6s at the Lake!
content.protection: Starts with small, somewhat sparse gear, and continues with great finger- & hand-sized gear above.
content.location: The major dihedral of Lost Temple rock.

content.description: Over on left side of Lost Temple Rock mini amp area, left of Lost Temple Corner.  Climb broken rock to ledges then left up into "the funnel" and up rib to top.  Climber is forced to left of rib just a bit to make moves on upper section.  Difficulty rises if you stay right on rib or even right of it.  Upper moves of this rib part of the climb are unique.
content.protection: Good at start and through "the funnel" but perhaps nil above.
content.location: Lost Temple Rock on its left margin.

content.description: Hand traverse from near the start of "The Doom" to the corner.  Continue up, staying on or just left of the corner
content.location: The outside corner to the right of Lost Temple Corner.

content.description: "The Doom" goes up the dihedral to the roof, then out the right side.  A very technical little route.
content.location: On the right side of Lost Temple rock is a low roof.

content.description:
Climb the dihedral and crack to the overgrown ledge. Similar to the upper half of Surely Temple, stemming works well most of the way. It's a good climb to do if you get tired of struggling on The Doom next door.

 This is unnamed #17 in Swartling/Mayer.
content.location: Located on the right end of the crag. It's the obvious inside corner with a deep wide crack just a few feet right of The Doom.

pathTokens: East Bluff 03 - West of the Quarry

content.description:
Lost Temple rock is a surprisingly tall crag (for DL) with a soaring dihedral at its center.  It is seldom visited because finding it involves skirting the edge of the quarry, there is no trail, and the slope underneath it is heavily guarded by loose rocks and wild raspberries.  But for those who enjoy getting off-trail and climbing in seclusion, this is one of the quickest quarry-area rocks to reach. 

  Lost Temple classics include "Lost Temple Corner," "Faith, Hope, and Tension," and "The Doom."
